    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BRAKE BOOSTER AND MASTER CYLINDER - ROAD TESTING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ROAD TESTING</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Before road testing a vehicle, depress brake pedal to be sure that pedal travel is normal. Make a
                    series of low speed stops to be sure brakes are functioning.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <para>Road test vehicle and check general operation of the brake system for the following:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Too much Pedal Travel</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Vibrating or Pulsating Pedal</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Spongy or Springy Pedal</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Hard Pedal</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Drag</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Slow or incomplete brake pedal return when power steering fluid has reached normal operating
                    temperature of 125 to 135 degrees F.
                </para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>If any of the above conditions are noted, refer to
            <hotlnk document="s04017y_X0401705.xml" xrefid="x0401705">TROUBLESHOOTING</hotlnk>
            , and perform required service to correct problem.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
